{"id":684724,"date":"2025-02-08T10:08:56","date_gmt":"2025-02-08T04:38:56","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/?p=684724"},"modified":"2025-09-18T18:06:32","modified_gmt":"2025-09-18T12:36:32","slug":"which-ba-degree-is-best-for-upsc-aspirants","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/which-ba-degree-is-best-for-upsc-aspirants","title":{"rendered":"Which BA is best for UPSC aspirants?"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>The Union Public Service Commission, UPSC, is one of the most competitive exams in India for various governmental posts, such as the Indian Administrative Service (IAS), the Indian Police Service (IPS), and the Indian Foreign Service (IFS). The UPSC exam is a pillar for anyone who wants to work in public service; it demands students to possess analytical prowess, general knowledge, and mastery in a lot of subjects across the board. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing the right degree is a crucial step for UPSC aspirants, as it lays the foundation for a strong preparation strategy. If you\u2019re wondering which degree is best for UPSC, a Bachelor of Arts (BA) is often the preferred choice due to its alignment with the UPSC syllabus. But which BA course is best for UPSC? A program that covers subjects like Political Science, History, and Public Administration can give you an edge. With the flexibility of online degrees, many aspirants now opt for programs that allow them to balance studies and UPSC preparation. If you\u2019re considering an online BA program, Sikkim Manipal University offers a UGC-recognized degree that is valid for UPSC and designed to support your IAS ambitions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\">A complete list of BA subjects: Specializations, syllabus and more<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Best BA course for UPSC<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing the right BA degree is a good starting point for an aspiring IAS officer since this degree is designed to align directly with the UPSC curriculum. Here are some of the most popular BA programs that not only build relevant knowledge but also enhance analytical abilities beneficial for the UPSC exam:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>BA in Political Science<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/bachelor-of-arts-political-science\">Political science<\/a> deals with themes of governance, international relations, public administration, and dynamics of Indian politics, which are incorporated into the General Studies subject and optional syllabi of UPSC.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>This degree provides students with knowledge in political theory, government running, and fundamental ideologies, which are important for UPSC.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"2\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>BA in History<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>This program focuses on ancient, medieval, and modern Indian history and assists candidates in understanding the historical Indian background.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It helps students develop their historical time perspective to answer questions on Indian heritage and world history in the UPSC syllabus.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"3\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>BA in Economics<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Economics offers information on the structure of the Indian economy, national and international policies, development frameworks, and budget planning.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Economic development, budgeting, and statistics are part of UPSC exams, so having a degree in this field might prove beneficial, especially when the student decides to take up Economics as an optional subject.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"4\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>BA in Geography<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Geography is part of General Studies as well as an optional subject of the UPSC civil services examination.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>This degree involves physical and human geography, which is useful in answering questions on world and Indian geography and climate, which are all important UPSC areas.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"5\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>BA in Sociology<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/career-options-after-ba-sociology\">Sociology<\/a> is the study of social institutions and cultural and societal issues.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Subjects involving population analysis, social organizations, and emerging questions like poverty levels or urbanization draw a close resemblance to the UPSC General Studies and essay sections.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"6\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>BA in Public Administration<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Public administration examines the processes through which governments are run, decisions and actions are made and implemented, and problems are solved or prevented.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Since public administration is applicable to government agency operations, it may prove useful to students who wish to join the civil service as administrators.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Eligibility of UPSC exams<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>UPSC Eligibility Criteria<\/strong><\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\">Age Limit<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\">21 to 32 years<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\">Age Relaxation<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\">OBC &#8211; 3 yearsSC\/ST &#8211; 5 years<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\">Minimum Educational Qualification<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\">Graduation<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\">Number of Attempts<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\">General\/EWS &#8211; 6OBC\/PwBD &#8211; 9SC\/ST &#8211; unlimited<\/td><\/tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\">Nationality<\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\">Indian<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>UPSC qualification<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Educational:<\/strong> A degree from a recognized university<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Final-year Candidates:<\/strong> Eligible for Prelims but must prove qualification for Mains<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Professionals with Govt.-recognized qualifications:<\/strong> Eligible<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Medical Students (MBBS final year):<\/strong> Eligible if they submit course completion proof<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>UPSC nationality criteria<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>IAS, IPS, IFS:<\/strong> Indian citizen<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Other Services:<\/strong> Indian citizens or specific categories from Nepal, Bhutan, or certain other countries intending to settle in India<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>UPSC attempt limits<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>General Category:<\/strong> 6 attempts until 32 years<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>OBC:<\/strong> 9 attempts until 35 years<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SC\/ST:<\/strong> Unlimited until 37 years<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>PwBD:<\/strong> 9 attempts until 42 years<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>EWS:<\/strong> 6 attempts until 32 years<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Restrictions on applying for UPSC exam<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>IAS\/IFS Officers:<\/strong> Cannot reappear once appointed<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>IPS Officers:<\/strong> Cannot select IPS if already appointed<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>UPSC physical eligibility<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Physical Fitness:<\/strong> Necessary for roles like IAS and IPS<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Medical Test:<\/strong> Required for successful CSE candidates<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Physical Standards:<\/strong> Height, weight, and chest measurements for IPS and certain other services as per UPSC guidelines<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Choosing the right BA course for UPSC<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Interest is the first condition when selecting a BA specialization; then comes the degree curriculum\u2019s compatibility with the UPSC syllabus. A program that teaches overlapping <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/most-preferred-optional-subjects-for-upsc-mains\"><strong>BA subjects for UPSC success<\/strong><\/a> should be preferred, as it offers a competitive advantage when studying for the UPSC.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To make the right decision on which optional subjects to go for in UPSC, you have to find out which of the optional subjects are similar to the BA course that you have chosen. For example, Political Science, History, Geography, and Sociology are popular BA streams suited for UPSC. Based on your interest and each subject\u2019s curriculum and relevance in UPSC, you can opt for any area of your choice.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>UPSC toppers with BA degree<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table is-style-stripes\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th>Toppers<\/th><th>Year<\/th><th>Degree<\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>Iqbal Dhaliwal<\/td><td>1995<\/td><td>BA Economics<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Mona Pruthi<\/td><td>2005<\/td><td>BA Economics<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Tina Dabi<\/td><td>2015<\/td><td>BA Political Science<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Shruti Sharma<\/td><td>2021<\/td><td>BA History<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Is an online degree valid for UPSC?<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With the growing popularity of flexible learning, many aspirants wonder, <strong>\u201cIs an online degree eligible for UPSC?\u201d<\/strong> The good news is that the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) accepts degrees obtained through online and distance learning, provided they are recognized by the University Grants Commission (UGC) and awarded by a university approved by the Distance Education Bureau (DEB).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are considering an online BA program, ensure that the university is UGC-DEB approved to avoid any eligibility issues. A credible online degree, like the BA program offered by Sikkim Manipal University, meets these criteria, making it a valid and accepted qualification for UPSC exams.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The following are the criteria for online degrees to be valid for UPSC-<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Recognition of the institution<\/strong>:<br>The online degree must be from a recognized institution approved by the UGC for offering online or distance education.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Minimum educational qualification for UPSC<\/strong>:<br>Candidates must have a bachelor\u2019s degree in any discipline from a recognized university. Online or regular mode doesn&#8217;t matter as long as the university is recognized.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Verification<\/strong>:<br>During document verification in later stages of the selection process, the degree certificate and university recognition will be scrutinized. Ensure that your degree and the mode of study comply with the eligibility norms.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Opting for an <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/\"><strong>online degree<\/strong><\/a> can be a great advantage for UPSC aspirants, as it allows flexibility in study schedules, enabling focused preparation for the Civil Services Examination while earning a recognized qualification.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Pursue online BA from SMU while you prepare for UPSC<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-ba-degree-smu\"><strong>online Bachelor of Arts (BA)<\/strong><\/a> offered at Sikkim Manipal University (SMU) is a program that aims to offer learners core knowledge in English, Sociology, and Political Science. This program is fully online and UGC-entitled, and SMU has a NAAC A+ accreditation. This means the course curriculum and delivery method meet national educational standards.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The course ensures students get a quality education similar to that provided in the traditional offline mode. By the end of the online BA, students become experts in the specialization field. It makes them well-equipped to handle various careers that require decision-making, the ability to work well with people, and good communication skills.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Degree<\/strong>: Bachelor of Arts (BA) with combination of English, Sociology, and Political Science<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Institution<\/strong>: Sikkim Manipal University (SMU)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Accreditation<\/strong>: UGC-entitled, NAAC A+<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Duration<\/strong>: 36 months<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Eligibility<\/strong>: 10+2<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Fee<\/strong>: INR 13,500 per semester (Total INR 81,000); EMI starts at INR 2,083\/month<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Conclusion<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Selecting the correct BA degree can be one of the first and most significant moves to UPSC as it provides candidates with knowledge of areas that are similar to the UPSC syllabus. Given that the UPSC is a professional examination, programs such as SMU\u2019s online BA allow aspirants to further their education while preparing for the test and, in the long run, their careers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Union Public Service Commission, UPSC, is one of the most competitive exams in India for various governmental posts, such as the Indian Administrative Service (IAS), the Indian Police Service (IPS), and the Indian Foreign Service (IFS). The UPSC exam is a pillar for anyone who wants to work in public service; it demands students [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":19,"featured_media":684573,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[609],"tags":[265,219,19,280],"class_list":["post-684724","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-bachelor-of-arts","tag-bachelor-of-arts","tag-online-bachelor-of-arts","tag-online-degree","tag-upsc"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v27.5 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/product\/yoast-seo-wordpress\/ -->\n<title>Which is the best BA degree for UPSC aspirants - Online Manipal<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Which BA course is best for UPSC aspirants? Read this blog to find out which BA degree you should choose for UPSC exams.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/684724\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_GB\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Which is the best BA degree for UPSC aspirants - Online Manipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Which BA course is best for UPSC aspirants? Read this blog to find out which BA degree you should choose for UPSC exams.\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/which-ba-degree-is-best-for-upsc-aspirants\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"Online Manipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:publisher\" content=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/onlinemanipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:published_time\" content=\"2025-02-08T04:38:56+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:modified_time\" content=\"2025-09-18T12:36:32+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/MCA-MAHE-Increase-earning-potential.jpg\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:width\" content=\"1200\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:height\" content=\"600\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:type\" content=\"image\/jpeg\" \/>\n<meta name=\"author\" content=\"Editorial Team\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary_large_image\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:label1\" content=\"Written by\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:data1\" content=\"Editorial Team\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:label2\" content=\"Estimated reading time\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:data2\" content=\"7 minutes\" \/>\n<script type=\"application\/ld+json\" class=\"yoast-schema-graph\">{\"@context\":\"https:\\\/\\\/schema.org\",\"@graph\":[{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/which-ba-degree-is-best-for-upsc-aspirants\",\"url\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/which-ba-degree-is-best-for-upsc-aspirants\",\"name\":\"Which is the best BA degree for UPSC aspirants - Online Manipal\",\"isPartOf\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/#website\"},\"primaryImageOfPage\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/which-ba-degree-is-best-for-upsc-aspirants#primaryimage\"},\"image\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/which-ba-degree-is-best-for-upsc-aspirants#primaryimage\"},\"thumbnailUrl\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/wp-content\\\/uploads\\\/2024\\\/03\\\/MCA-MAHE-Increase-earning-potential.jpg\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-02-08T04:38:56+00:00\",\"dateModified\":\"2025-09-18T12:36:32+00:00\",\"description\":\"Which BA course is best for UPSC aspirants? Read this blog to find out which BA degree you should choose for UPSC exams.\",\"breadcrumb\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/which-ba-degree-is-best-for-upsc-aspirants#breadcrumb\"},\"inLanguage\":\"en-GB\",\"potentialAction\":[{\"@type\":\"ReadAction\",\"target\":[\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/which-ba-degree-is-best-for-upsc-aspirants\"]}]},{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"inLanguage\":\"en-GB\",\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/which-ba-degree-is-best-for-upsc-aspirants#primaryimage\",\"url\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/wp-content\\\/uploads\\\/2024\\\/03\\\/MCA-MAHE-Increase-earning-potential.jpg\",\"contentUrl\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/wp-content\\\/uploads\\\/2024\\\/03\\\/MCA-MAHE-Increase-earning-potential.jpg\",\"width\":1200,\"height\":600,\"caption\":\"PR job roles\"},{\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/which-ba-degree-is-best-for-upsc-aspirants#breadcrumb\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Which BA is best for UPSC aspirants?\"}]},{\"@type\":\"WebSite\",\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/#website\",\"url\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/\",\"name\":\"Online Manipal\",\"description\":\"Online Manipal\",\"publisher\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/#organization\"},\"potentialAction\":[{\"@type\":\"SearchAction\",\"target\":{\"@type\":\"EntryPoint\",\"urlTemplate\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/?s={search_term_string}\"},\"query-input\":{\"@type\":\"PropertyV